25/01/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The European Commission (EC) announced on Wednesday (January 24th) that it has endorsed regional aid maps for Bulgaria, Cyprus and Romania for the period 2007-2013. The documents were prepared in part under the new Regional Aid Guidelines, which envision shifting aid to the most deprived regions of the enlarged EU, to boost competitiveness and provide for a smooth transition. 
Separately Wednesday, Turkish State Minister Kursad Tuzmen arrived on an official two-day visit to Bulgaria. After talks with government officials in Sofia, he announced an agreement to boost bilateral co-operation in the veterinary sector, customs and railway transport. (EU website, BNR - 24/01/07)
